age in 2022" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-already-working-on-next-album-news.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-already-working-on-next-album-news-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-already-working-on-next-album-news-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-already-working-on-next-album-news-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-already-working-on-next-album-news-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-already-working-on-next-album-news-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mick-jagger">Mick Jagger</a> has revealed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-rolling-stones">The Rolling Stones</a> are already at work on their next full-length album.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">The legendary band announced their 24th studio record, &#39;Hackney Diamonds&#39;</a> , last week (September 6) and shared its lead single, &#39;Angry&#39;. Following on from 2005&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-the-rolling-stones-7763-312997#:~:text=This%20is%20an%20old%2Dfashioned,well%20be%20by%20Sheryl%20Crow.">&#39;A Bigger Bang&#39;</a> , the LP will mark the Stones&#39; first collection of original music in 18 years.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-rolling-stones-new-album-release-date-hackney-diamonds-3494545">The Rolling Stones&#39; return is an even bigger bang</a></strong></li></ul><p> During a new interview with <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/09/14/arts/music/rolling-stones-hackney-diamonds.html?unlocked_article_code=3S-gAWgLaDmgjFJ_ji05pPtSWIiJnUn--1DGjVOKG2HA7HZkPVUBr0wo7WK6rzjUIFPrds6xPS_GfA_bXiLWU0T_Fm8FRLwoTXY8K48nZDzKM_W1DKeAfolYg7RouelwY5AAUtz3OyU_l5DC1r7lXgLpMHFxSGOWTrTL6KZZP2sXnXY18wGRLYcUX3e0B3KcasQAjc2aqFl7S0ogPUx6lC9Q1s1A2lafZs17agQbnynTTHwoIu9tWN3OMLrvUvXK77LWCHMlNBciLZZLSq1_tRUPoMJRLKvqdN_uMcOGj9Fo1RNTm6njpomdEoyYcXfma8brNXhu6bbGxfR0p2tlMYKwAHifNmbJixUYDg&amp;smid=nytcore-android-share" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>the New York Times</em></a> , Jagger and co. talked about how their forthcoming album ushers in a new chapter. “With <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/charlie-watts">Charlie [Watts]</a> leaving us, I think we needed to make a new mark with Steve [Jordan, drummer],” <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/keith-richards">Keith Richards</a> told the outlet.</p><p> Jagger then added that he doesn&#39;t think &#39;Hackney Diamonds&#39; will be “the last Rolling Stones album”, before confirming that a follow-up is currently in the works. “We&#39;ve got almost three-quarters through the next one,” he said.</p><p> The article goes on to note how the lyrics to &#39;Hackney Diamonds&#39; song &#39;Tell Me Straight&#39; seemingly allude to endings: “ <em>I need an answer/ How long can this last?/ Don&#39;t make me wait/ Is my future all in my past?</em> ”</p><p> The Rolling Stones also revealed recently that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-reveal-charlie-watts-appears-on-two-tracks-of-new-album-hackney-diamonds-3494170">two tracks on the LP will feature their late drummer Watts</a> . Both cuts – titled &#39;Mess It Up&#39; and &#39;Live By The Sword&#39; – were recorded in 2019. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="滚石乐队 - 愤怒（官方视频）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_mEC54eTuGw?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> &#39;Hackney Diamonds&#39; was recorded in various locations including Henson Recording Studios in Los Angeles, London&#39;s Metropolis Studios, Sanctuary Studios in the Bahamas, Electric Lady Studios and The Hit Factory/Germano Studios in New York.</p><p> “I don&#39;t want to be big-headed but we wouldn&#39;t have put this album out if we hadn&#39;t really liked it,” Jagger explained during a livestreamed conference last week. “We said we had to make a record we really love ourselves.</p><p> “We are quite pleased with it. We are not big-headed about it, but we hope you all like it.”</p><p> Elsewhere in the conversation, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-explain-meaning-of-new-hackney-diamonds-album-name-3494480">the band explained the meaning behind the album&#39;s title</a> after host Jimmy Fallon asked them if it was “a type of slang”.</p><p> &#39;Hackney Diamonds&#39; is due for release on October 20 in various formats – <a href="https://therollingstones.lnk.to/HackneyDiamondsPR" target="_blank" rel="noopener">you can pre-order/pre-save it here</a> .</p><p> The Rolling Stones&#39; most recent album came in the form of a blues covers LP, <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/rolling-stones-blue-lonesome-1882686#:~:text=These%2012%20tracks%20were%20recorded,but%20not%20wanting%20for%20thrills.">&#39;Blue &amp; Lonesome&#39;</a> , in 2016.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-are-already-working-on-their-next-album-3498047">The Rolling Stones are already working on their next album</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
